What Happens to a School Shooter’s Sister?

Twenty-five years ago, Kristin Kinkel’s brother, Kip, killed their parents and opened fire at their high school. Today, she is close with Kip —and still reckoning with his crimes. “I love my brother more than I ever thought possible,” she once told a judge. Jennifer Gonnerman reports.
